|GKB-- Living Vines ----------------------------------------------|000

|CKBCommand:|000 vines <mode|off>
|CKBGuild Level:|000 3
|CKBCurrent:|000 Tellurian

Living Vines is a sustained combat invocation.  Once invoked, the
vines coil around your steps and become part of your combat rhythm.
During combat rounds they may lash the target you are attacking.  When
you are struck, they may also twist defensively around the attacker,
fouling footing or punishing the blow.

Use:

  |CKBvines|000              Show current mode and unlocked modes.
  |CKBvines lash|000         Basic striking vines.
  |CKBvines venom|000        Toxic sap and poison-tinged lashes.
  |CKBvines barbs|000        Stronger thorned retaliation.
  |CKBvines snare|000        Entangling roots that hinder movement.
  |CKBvines off|000          Dismiss the vines.

Lash is available when you first learn the invocation.  Venom, barbs,
and snare unlock as your training and guild level grow.  Mastery makes
the vines more efficient and more likely to answer during combat.

Mode unlocks:

  |CKBlash|000     When you learn Living Vines.
  |CKBvenom|000    Training 2, or Druid guild level 8.
  |CKBbarbs|000    Training 3, or Druid guild level 14.
  |CKBsnare|000    Training 4, or Druid guild level 20.

Living Vines spends Tellurian nwyfre when it lashes.  If your Tellurian
current runs dry, the vines will sink back into the earth.
